<section sectnbr = "5B">
<servcat sctnbr = "05" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A5206015" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "02" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Manual Transaxle Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206010">Manual Transaxle Unit Dismounting and Remounting</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206014">Manual Transaxle Assembly Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A5206015001">
<title>
Disassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove back up light switch. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A5206007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove gear shift and select shaft assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A5206012"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove transaxle case bolts.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove transaxle left side case (1) from right case using special tool.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B007">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09912-34510">
09912–34510
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAY301520026.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "55.580mm" ver = "01" gw = "165" gh = "141"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove reverse gear shift lever bolts (1) and reverse gear shift lever (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0B520024.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "70.640mm" ver = "01" gw = "168" gh = "184"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tapping input shaft end with plastic hammer, push it out as assembly from case a little, and then remove input shaft assembly (1), countershaft assembly (2), high speed gear shift shaft (3), low speed gear shift shaft (4), 5th and 6th gear shift shaft (5), reverse gear shift shaft (6) and reverse gears (7).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0B520025.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "59.208mm" ver = "01" gw = "159" gh = "151"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove differential assembly from transaxle right case.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A5206015002">
<title>
Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206016">Transaxle Right Case Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206017">Transaxle Left Case Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206019">Input Shaft Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206022">Countershaft Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206029">Differential Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206027">Gear Shift Shaft and Fork Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install differential assembly into transaxle right case.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Join input shaft assembly (5), countershaft assembly (4), low speed gear shift shaft (2), high speed gear shift shaft (3), 5th and 6th gear shift shaft (6), reverse gear shift shaft (7) and reverse gears (8) all together, then install them into transaxle right case (1) so as not to damage oil seal by input shaft spline.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Input shaft right bearing on shaft can be installed into transaxle right case (1) by tapping shaft with plastic hammer.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Make sure that countershaft is engaged with final gear while installing.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0B520026.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "64.257mm" ver = "01" gw = "161" gh = "166"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Select input shaft shim and reverse gear shim as follows.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Measure depth “a” of transaxle left case (1) and “b” of transaxle right case (2) and measure depth “e” of transaxle left case and “f” of transaxle right case.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Measure distance “c” of input shaft assembly (3) and measure distance “g” of reverse gear assembly (4).
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Calculate the clearance of “d” and “h” by the following formulas.
</ptxt>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "1" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "3.426in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Clearance “d” = Depth “a” + Depth “b” – Distance “c”
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "1" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "3.426in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Clearance “h” = Depth “e” + Depth “f” – Distance “g”
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAY301520064.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "95.831mm" ver = "01" gw = "161" gh = "255"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<c-change/>
<s2>
