<s1>
<ptxt>
Install input shaft shim (1) and reverse gear shim (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAW101520023.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "75.134mm" ver = "01" gw = "172" gh = "196"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install reverse gear shift lever (1) and then tighten new reverse gear shift lever bolts (2) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
The reverse gear shift lever bolts are pre-coated with adhesive. If these bolts are reused, they may work loose.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Be sure to replace the reverse gear shift lever bolts with new ones whenever they are removed.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T5B012">
<t-part>
Reverse gear shift lever bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
23
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
17.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAY301520028.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "72.931mm" ver = "01" gw = "169" gh = "190"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean mating surfaces of both right and left cases, and apply sealant to transaxle right case (1) as shown in figure. Diameter of applied sealant is 1.5 mm (0.059 in.).
</ptxt>
<materials>
<materialitem name = "SUZUKI Bond No.1217G" id = "M5B006" uid = "-491504098">
<m-part>
“A”
</m-part>
<m-desc>
Sealant
</m-desc>
<m-number>
99000–31260
</m-number>
<m-name>
SUZUKI Bond No.1217G
</m-name>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</materialitem>
</materials>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Mate it with transaxle left case (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten transaxle case bolts (3) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T5B013">
<t-part>
Transaxle case bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
23
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
17.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0B520030.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "90.328mm" ver = "01" gw = "146" gh = "239"/>
</figure>
</s1>
